My husband and I both got sick with the same bug this year (same specific symptoms), and that&#39;s rare... but I&#39;m not too worried about the latest &quot;superbug&quot;, that&#39;s what they seem to be saying all the time ever since I started watching the news as a child (90s), it&#39;s like they&#39;re always trying to sensationalize.... I don&#39;t think it&#39;s funny anymore...  kids especially don&#39;t think the news is funny.... I remember when I was maybe like ten and they had a short blurb at the end of the news about possible asteriod... I was so freaked out my mom had to fill a bowl with water take an egg out of the fridge, and slide it down the bowl into the water, and say that if it hits, that&#39;s what will happen to it, it will simply slide into the ocean... and I bought it too... lol!

